data.name: [TIE-617] Integrate Microsoft Teams with RingCentral
data.notes:
Summary

This task involves integrating RingCentral telephony and meeting capabilities with Microsoft Teams and Outlook to provide the Sales team with unified communication tools. The integration will enable calling, messaging, and meeting functionality directly within the Microsoft ecosystem while ensuring all interactions are captured in RingSense for coaching and AI analysis.

Value or Impact

Operational Value: Eliminates context switching between multiple communication platforms, improving Sales team efficiency and response times.
Productivity Impact: Enables Sales agents to handle all communication (calls, SMS, meetings) from within familiar Microsoft tools.
Strategic Value: RingSense integration provides AI-powered coaching insights and performance tracking for continuous improvement.
Affected Users: Sales team members and Sales Managers (10-49 users impacted).

Acceptance Criteria

    Sales agents can place and receive calls through Teams using RingCentral telephony
    Call history, voicemails, and SMS are accessible within Teams interface
    Meeting scheduling works seamlessly between Outlook and RingCentral
    All calls are captured in RingSense for coaching and AI tracking
    Presence sync between Teams and RingCentral is functional
    Unified contact lists from both Microsoft and RingCentral systems are available
    Click-to-dial functionality is properly documented as not supported (per Alex's research)

Technical Details

Azure AD Requirements:    Global admin roles in Azure AD and Exchange Online
    App registration with OAuth permissions (Calendars.ReadWrite, User.ReadBasic.All)
    Admin consent flow configuration
    TLS and network settings for Microsoft Graph endpoints

Exchange Online Configuration:

    Service account with application impersonation rights
    OAuth connection in RingCentral Admin Portal (Tenant ID, Client ID, Client Secret)
    Calendar folder mapping for RingCentral Meetings

Teams Integration:

    Teams Admin Center policy configuration
    App permission policy for RingCentral personal/pinned apps
    Tenant app setup policy for auto-installation
    RingCentral for Teams app deployment

Network Requirements:

    Ports: TCP/UDP 5004-5005, 443 for signaling, 3478 for STUN/TURN
    Bandwidth planning and QoS configuration
    Firewall rules for RingCentral services

Affected Systems / Integrations

    Azure Active Directory
    Microsoft Teams Admin Center
    Exchange Online
    RingCentral Admin Portal
    RingCentral Meetings
    RingSense (for call recording and AI analysis)
    Outlook (Classic and New versions)
    Microsoft 365 Admin Center

Next Steps or Analyst Notes

Current Status: Initial testing completed by Alexander Eakins. RingCentral for Teams installed successfully. Identified that click-to-dial won't work in this environment - Teams app should be used for meetings/recording only, not cold dialing.

Key Findings:

    RingCentral for Outlook app deemed unnecessary (native scheduling already works in Outlook Classic)
    COM Add-ins disabled in Outlook (new) affecting integration options
    Project requires comprehensive coordination across multiple systems as detailed by Daniel DeZago

Pending Decisions:

    Confirm scope includes all client-facing Teams users, not just Sales
    Establish MVP requirements vs full implementation
    Determine if this aligns with current pilot program mentioned by Matt Lincoln

Next Actions:

    Obtain necessary admin credentials for all systems
    Register RingCentral app in Azure AD tenant
    Configure service account impersonation in Exchange Online
    Deploy Outlook add-in via Centralized Deployment
    Push RingCentral app to Sales/Sales Managers Teams with proper policies
    Assign licenses and configure default meeting settings

----------------------------------------

Original Description (Retained)

Description of Change:
Integrate Microsoft Teams and Outlook with RingCentral to enable seamless calling, messaging, and meeting capabilities for Sales team and Sales Managers.

User Story:
As a Sales team member, I want RingCentral integrated with Microsoft Teams and Outlook so that I can make calls, send SMS/fax, manage voicemails, and schedule meetings from within the Microsoft ecosystem while having all interactions tracked in RingSense for coaching and AI analysis.

Success Criteria:

    Sales agents can place and receive calls through Teams using RingCentral telephony
    Call history, voicemails, and SMS are accessible within Teams interface
    Meeting scheduling works seamlessly between Outlook and RingCentral
    All calls are captured in RingSense for coaching and AI tracking
    Presence sync between Teams and RingCentral
    Unified contact lists from both Microsoft and RingCentral systems

Technical Requirements:

    Azure AD app registration with proper permissions
    Exchange Online calendar integration with service account
    Teams Admin Center policy configuration
    RingCentral Admin Portal OAuth setup
    Centralized deployment of Outlook add-ins
    Network configuration for proper call routing
